---
/**
 * ai-agents 0002 · Figure 1 — "Runtime orchestrates the LLM loop".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/ai-agents/lessons/0002-agent-runtime-and-context.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 * In an .astro file the SVG is plain HTML, so it renders byte-for-byte.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers ONCE in a shared <defs> block in
 * the document <body> (ids: arw, arwA, arwG, arwR). The MDX has no such shared
 * block, so the markers this figure references are inlined into its own <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 580 220"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Runtime orchestrates: User to Runtime to LLM, with tools below LLM, a loop-back from LLM to Runtime, and a halt arrow from Runtime to the right"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <!-- User box -->
            <rect x="10" y="20" width="90" height="44" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text
                x="55"
                y="40"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">User</text
            >
            <text
                x="55"
                y="56"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="10"
                fill="#6b675f">request</text
            >

            <!-- Arrow: User -> Runtime -->
            <line x1="102" y1="42" x2="148" y2="42" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>

            <!-- Runtime box (highlighted, dashed border) -->
            <rect
                x="150"
                y="8"
                width="200"
                height="68"
                rx="10"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                stroke-dasharray="6 3"></rect>
            <text
                x="250"
                y="30"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">Runtime</text
            >
            <text
                x="250"
                y="50"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                fill="#6b675f">loop · tools · retry · limits</text
            >
            <text
                x="250"
                y="66"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="9"
                fill="#6b675f">cost control · safety</text
            >

            <!-- Arrow: Runtime -> LLM -->
            <line
                x1="250"
                y1="78"
                x2="250"
                y2="114"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.2"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>

            <!-- LLM box -->
            <rect
                x="186"
                y="116"
                width="128"
                height="44"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="250"
                y="136"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="14"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">LLM</text
            >
            <text
                x="250"
                y="152"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="9.5"
                fill="#6b675f">predicts only</text
            >

            <!-- Loop-back dashed arrow: LLM result -> Runtime -->
            <path
                d="M 186 130 C 140 130, 130 90, 150 55"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-dasharray="4 3"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <text x="106" y="100" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#7a1f12">result</text>

            <!-- Halt arrow: Runtime -> right -->
            <line
                x1="352"
                y1="32"
                x2="430"
                y2="32"
                stroke="#9a2417"
                stroke-width="1.2"
                marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
            <text x="391" y="24" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9a2417"
                >halt / cost limit</text
            >

            <!-- Tool boxes below LLM -->
            <rect x="60" y="178" width="110" height="36" rx="7" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="115"
                y="200"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#2f5d3a">File System</text
            >

            <rect x="195" y="178" width="110" height="36" rx="7" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="250"
                y="200"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#2f5d3a">External API</text
            >

            <rect x="330" y="178" width="110" height="36" rx="7" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="385"
                y="200"
                text-anchor="middle"
                dominant-baseline="middle"
                font-size="11"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Database</text
            >

            <!-- Arrows: LLM -> tools -->
            <line x1="215" y1="162" x2="155" y2="176" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="250" y1="162" x2="250" y2="176" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="285" y1="162" x2="345" y2="176" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        The runtime is the application server around the LLM. It runs the loop. The LLM only
        predicts; everything else &#8212; calling tools, retrying, enforcing limits &#8212; is the
        runtime's job.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
